messages.content:
Responsibilities

Improve design and presentation of corporate information including sales collateral, factsheets, images, illustrations, infographics to represent corporate data and information in more impactful ways;
Design customised graphics for use on our website and sales collateral;
Ensure all design standards are on brand and adhering to the overall guidelines;
Deliver artifacts that set the standard for design excellence, from ideation to prototypes to validate; 
Work with other project stakeholders to deliver the information architecture, user story, customer journey map and wireframe flow for new production projects; 
Actively conduct user interface reviews during engineering development phase to ensure built quality; 
Regular review of usage data to analyze user behavior and pain points; 
Participating in key internal meetings including weekly status updates and planning sessions. 


 Qualifications

Bachelor's degree in Design, Human-Computer Interaction, Computer Science, a related field, or equivalent practical experience.
3 years of experience in product design.
Experience implementing visual design systems across platforms in an iterative software development environment, applying design tools (e.g. Figma, Photoshop, Illustrator, Sketch).
A portfolio highlighting multiple projects and your direct contributions.
